[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Written evidence from ASLEF (SLC 008)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]Summary[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]ASLEF policy 
[normal]is ideally; all level crossings should be closed.
[normal]If full barrier crossings retained, should be fitted with obstacle detectors.
[normal]Welcome the review of legislation by the Law Commissions.
[normal]Network Rail to have a programme to close the one third of level cross
[normal]ings that are within 200m of an alternative.
[normal]Welcome Network Rail’s positive changes to the risk assessment process.
[normal]Risk assessment should be used to prioritise resources, and closures.
[normal]Support use of fixed and mobile CCTV by Ne
[normal]twork Rail and the British 
[normal]T
[normal]ransport Police.
[normal]Support awareness campaign on level crossing safety
[normal]Seek ways of deterring offenders, including increased fines, licences being endorsed, but also support BTP driver awareness courses
[normal]Support TUC and affiliated Trade Unions in promoting the use of the HSE guidance 
[normal] Driving at work Managing work-related road safety
[normal] (INDG382)
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The 
[normal]Transport Committee into safety on level crossings has requested 
[normal]written evidence on the following points:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Are current safety measures at level crossings adequate? How should they be improved?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]In addition to bridges and underpasses what other cost-effective measures can be introduced to replace or improve safety at level crossings?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]How should expenditure on improving safety at level crossings be prioritised in r[bold]elation to other demands on the rail budget?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Is Network Rail giving sufficient priority to improving safety at level crossings?[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Is Government policy and regulatory action by the Office of Rail Regulation (ORR) in relation to safety at level crossings adequate? What more should the Government and ORR do?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How should the legislation governing level crossings be updated?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How should public awareness of safety at level crossings be improved?[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]“Does your route planning take sufficient account of overhead restrictions eg bridges and tunnels and other hazards, 
[normal]such as level crossings[bold], which may present dangers fo
[normal]r long vehicles?”. 
